title: Dost
subTitle: Maanav befriends Gopichand, a reformed thief, and helps him secure a job to turn his life around. However, Maanav suddenly disappears and returns just in time to support Gopichand during a crisis.

title: Aap To Aise Na The
subTitle: Vijay, who owns a furniture store, is in love with Varsha. However, Vijay's life takes a drastic turn when she decides to marry his friend Vikram, a rich man, who promises her a better life.

title: Narsingh Avatar
subTitle: Bringing the best in cinema.

title: Bhoomi Par Bhagwan
subTitle: Ranga, a reckless man, abducts Ganga, his previous lover and her husband and keeps them captive at his secret hideout location.

title: Chameli Ki Shaadi
subTitle: Charandas and Chameli develop feelings for each other. However, caste differences lead their families to oppose their budding relationship.

title: Hamara Khandan
subTitle: Vishal, who hails from a wealthy Hindu family, falls in love with Ruby, a poor Catholic girl. While her father approves of the marriage, his father does his best to stop them from marrying.

title: Mehbooba
subTitle: Suraj, a singer, takes refuge from a storm in a rest house. During his stay, he has a strange feeling that he has been there before and recalls memories of being with a woman called Ratna.

title: Pukar
subTitle: Major Jaidev saves a politician from the clutches of a dreaded terrorist. However, the terrorist joins hands with his childhood friend Anjali to ruin his life.

title: Kasam Suhaag Ki
subTitle: Troubles arise for Surajmukhi after her husband, Sultan, is gunned down and she and her daughter get abducted by goons. She tries her best to get revenge and escape with her child.

title: Kundan
subTitle: Thakur Shamsher Singh, a wealthy criminal, tries to befriend a newly-appointed police officer in order to gain his favour, only to find out that the policeman is immune to his tactics.

title: Kundan

title: Kunwara Baap
subTitle: A rickshaw driver's life changes when he finds an abandoned baby at his doorstep. When the child is affected by polio, he has a change of heart and decides to care for him.

title: Mehandi Ban Gai Khoon
subTitle: Jyoti and Prakash, a young couple, break up in order for the former's marriage with Vijay. However, when she gets tortured and thrown out of the house by her in-laws, she decides to take revenge.

title: Bhuvan Shome
subTitle: A lonely bureaucrat goes on holiday to a village in Gujarat where a young peasant woman helps him see beyond his job and develop a newfound empathy for people.

title: Woh 7 Din
subTitle: Anand, a doctor, realises that Maya, his wife, loves someone else but married him out of coercion. Thus, he sets out to reunite the lovers, but they don't want to be together anymore.

title: Aman
subTitle: Dr Gautamdas, a well-educated man from London, moves to Japan during the aftermath of the Hiroshima and Nagasaki bombing, where he falls in love with Meloda.

title: Pyaasa Sawan
subTitle: Chandrakant, a wealthy man, observes his son Ravi neglecting his wife for his career and decides to intervene to save Ravi's marriage.

title: Mother India
subTitle: Radha, a poor but righteous woman, struggles to raise her children opposing Sukhilala, a greedy moneylender. Despite the hurdles, she refuses to sacrifice her integrity.

title: Khatron Ke Khiladi
subTitle: Balwant, a truck driver, is driven into the underworld as he wants to take revenge on the owners of the trucking company for the death of his brother.

title: Dadagiri
subTitle: Barkha, a young heiress, is abused by her uncle and his family for her inheritance. Later, she runs away but is captured and taken back to her abusive relatives by her mother's ex-lover, Dharma.

title: Howrah Bridge
subTitle: Prem Kumar, a businessman who hails from Rangoon, commutes to Calcutta to find the killer of his brother and retrieve an invaluable family gift.

title: Dil Ne Phir Yaad Kiya
subTitle: Ashok, a salesman, is in love with Ashoo and wants to marry her. However, things take a turn when his brother kidnaps Ashoo.

title: Shirdi Ke Sai Baba
subTitle: A doctor who does not believe in Sai Baba's powers travels to Shirdi with his ill son. Soon, the doctor has to decide between Sai Baba and science to treat his ailing son.

title: Mard
subTitle: Azad, a wealthy prosperous king, is locked in a dungeon by General Dyer who wants to take over his kingdom. Years later, Azad's son comes to his father's rescue and puts an end to Dyer's tyranny.

title: Kranti
subTitle: Sanga, a devout employee of Raja Laxman Singh, is falsely accused of killing him. He escapes prison and forms a group of revolutionaries with the sole aim of driving the British out of India.

title: Roti Kapada Aur Makaan
subTitle: Bharat, a graduate and the eldest son of a poverty-stricken family, struggles to provide for his kin after his father's retirement.
